on is $2$.\n  We also construct an example to show that the approximation factor of their\nalgorithm for arbitrary submodular functions is $\\Omega(n/k)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 May 2023 20:05:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 May 2023 10:48:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-04"}
